location: Lake Worth, Palm Beach, South Florida
postcontent:
I have for sale a like new Trijicon Acog TA31 H RCO on a Larue LT681 Mount. It features a red illuminated horseshoe reticle with bullet drop compensator and Marine Corp ranging stadia lines. The Larue LT681 quick attach mount provides proper eye relief and access to the charging handle as well as absolute return to zero guaranteed. 

Comes in the shown Pelican case with scope cover, ARD Flashkill and all the manuals to go with it. Please contact me if you have any questions or would like more pictures.


About the ACOG;

Provides quick target acquisition at close combat ranges and out to 800 meters.
The TRIJICON ACOG 4x32 Scope, Army Rifle Combat Optic for the M150, TA51 Mount (TA31RCO-M150CP) was most recently chosen as the rifle combat optic of the U.S. Army. It provides the shooter with quick target acquisition at close combat ranges while providing enhanced target identification and hit probability out to 800 meters utilizing the Bullet Drop Compensator.

The Tritium illuminates the aiming point in total darkness, and the fiber optic self adjusts reticle brightness during daylight according to ambient light conditions. This allows the operator to keep both eyes open while engaging targets and maintaining maximum situational awareness.

The Trijicon ACOG 4x32 Scope incorporates the innovative Bindon Aiming Concept (BAC). This revolutionary, both-eyes-open aiming method provides you with "instinctive" target acquisition and increased hit potential. And, the scope's ranging is built into many of its reticles, so you only need to set zero once for a multitude of ranging distances.

Broad-band, anti-reflective coated lenses provide superior clarity and light gathering capabilities with zero distortion. The ACOG also offers large Eye Volume, giving you greater leeway - fore and aft, and from side to side - with which to see through the lens. Of course, once the target is acquired, the ACOG is a trusted ally to help you zero in on a perfect shot.

No tools are needed for windage and elevation adjustments because this ACOG scope features external windage and elevation adjusters, making it waterproof up to 11m without caps.

The ACOG is crafted with a tough, military-grade, aluminum-alloy housing and is waterproof to depths of 100 feet - making it nearly indestructible. Only the prism housing moves, so it's much more rugged than conventional designs.

postcontent:
Ok, ladies and gentlemen, what we have here is a Fausti Field Hunter. It's a gorgeous over/under 12 gauge Italian made shotgun. It's got a 28" barrel. I'm not sure what the official specs are, because I got the gun when I was around 18, so I've had it about 12 years now and the paperwork and choke tool have been lost with the ages. Not 100% certain if the specs on the chamber say 3" or 3.5". I managed to put a few 3.5" rounds through it last weekend and it didn't blow up on me, so we have that to work with. 

We've got a minor scratch on the stock, but that's about all I managed to find. It's had less than 100 rounds put through it over the course of its life. I took it out less than a week ago to triple check everything, and she's in perfect working order. She shoots well. Operated by firing pins, with a switch to control which pin goes. 

I'm asking $650 for the gun. I'm trying to cull down what I have, so I'm not looking for any trades, no matter how good they may seem to either of us. If you have any further questions, shoot me an email, but if you want me to get a whole lot more technical than what I've gotten in the ad then I'm afraid we're both up the creek. I also go to sleep early in the day through the week, so if you email me in the evening, I probably won't see it till late that night, but I will get back to you. She's a fine gun and would make an outstanding addition to anyone's collection.
